    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list function behavior\n\n### Summary\nThe function `m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list()` in `m2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c` was not behaving as expected when checking for PCI values in the eNB list. Added proper validation, bounds checking, and debug logging to help diagnose issues.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: \n  - Added MAX_NUM_CCs definition with default value\n  - Enhanced m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list() with input validation for PCI range (0-503)\n  - Added bounds checking for num_cc field\n  - Added debug logging to trace function execution\n  - Added comments about potential Nid_cell value interpretation issues\n  - Fixed minor whitespace formatting issues\n\nWhen calling m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list() with a valid PCI, the function now properly validates inputs and provides debug output to help identify why no matching eNB might be found. The function previously could access invalid memory or return incorrect results due to missing bounds checking on the num_cc field and Nid_cell array access.\n\nTo reproduce the issue, call m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list() with any PCI value and observe that without proper validation, the function could crash or return incorrect results when num_cc is invalid or when Nid_cell values are not properly populated.\n"
}